  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "The intuitive idea of the simplest SL configuration is the following: (1) Each client trains a neural network up to a specific layer (cut layer).",
    "(2) The output at that layer is sent to the server (or another client, depending on the configuration), which completes the training without seeing the raw data.",
    "This completes a round of forward propagation.",
    "(3) Gradients are backpropagated from the last layer to the cut layer.",
    "(4) Gradients in the cut layer are sent back to the initial client."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}